Load Json Data Into Staging Table Using SSIS 10

* SQL Server Integration Services (SSIS) is Used

*Using SSIS ToolBox, the following components will be drag in the Control Flow Dashboard;

  1. Drag Execute SQL Task.
  2. Drag Foreach Loop Container.
  3. Script Task will be drag inside the Foreach Loop Container.
  4. Data Flow Task will be drag inside the Foreach Loop Container


* Each Components in the Control Flow, is edited.

* Execute SQL Task

  1. Go to General.
  2. Add the Connection.
  3. Write SQL Statement.
  4. Click Ok.


*Create variables by right clicking the empty spot of the control flow or Data Flow Task Dashboard

*Variables is needed for the upcoming step.

  1. Create a variable for Json File Name as demonstrated.
  2. Create a variable for Json File Path as demonstrated.




*Foreach Loop Container

  1. Go to Collection.
  2. Browse the folder file name that contain json files.
  3. Write *.json to only load json file.
  4. Go to Variable Mappings.
  5. under Variable, select the User::JsonFilePath.
  6. Click on Ok



*Script Task 

  1. Go to Script.
  2. On ReadWriteVariables, Select the Variables that was created as shown below.
  3. Click on Edit Script to Insert the Code that is needed.


* Namespaces and Code for Script Task

  1. Make sure the right using Namespaces is Used.
  2. Code for Edit Script.
#region Namespaces
using System;
using System.Data;
using Microsoft.SqlServer.Dts.Runtime;
using System.Windows.Forms;
using System.IO;
#endregion
public void Main()

		{
            // TODO: Add your code here
            String strFullFileName;
            String strFileName;
            strFullFileName = Dts.Variables["User::JSONFilePath"].Value.ToString();
            strFileName = Path.GetFileName(strFullFileName);
            Dts.Variables["User::JSONFileName"].Value = strFileName;
            Dts.TaskResult = (int)ScriptResults.Success;
            
		}



* Using SSIS ToolBox, the following components will be drag in the Data Flow Task Dashboard.

* Each components of the Data Flow Task is edited.

* Namespaces and Code to load Json Files

#region Namespaces

using System;
using System.Data;
using Microsoft.SqlServer.Dts.Pipeline.Wrapper;
using Microsoft.SqlServer.Dts.Runtime.Wrapper;
using System.Web.Script.Serialization;
using System.IO;
using CollectionOfMovieNameSpace;
using System.Collections.Generic;
#endregion
       
 string filelocation = Variables.JSONFilePath;
        string jsonFileContent = File.ReadAllText(filelocation);
        //string jsonFileContent = File.ReadAllText(@"C:\Users\kedjo\OneDrive\Desktop\COLABERRY\ETLDWProject1\CSV_To_JSON\20200630BriefPerformanceofMovies.json");

       JavaScriptSerializer js = new JavaScriptSerializer() { MaxJsonLength = 86753090 };
            List<CollectionOfMovies> CollectionOfMovies = js.Deserialize<List<CollectionOfMovies>>(jsonFileContent);
            foreach (CollectionOfMovies CollectionOfMovie in CollectionOfMovies)
            {
                Output0Buffer.AddRow();
                Output0Buffer.Rank = CollectionOfMovie.Rank;
                Output0Buffer.Title = CollectionOfMovie.Title;
                Output0Buffer.LifeTimeGross = CollectionOfMovie.LifeTimeGross;
                Output0Buffer.Year = CollectionOfMovie.Year;
                Output0Buffer.MovieID = CollectionOfMovie.MovieID;
                Output0Buffer.Market = CollectionOfMovie.Market;
                Output0Buffer.TicketPriceName = CollectionOfMovie.TicketPriceName;
                Output0Buffer.CurrencyCode = CollectionOfMovie.CurrencyCode;
                Output0Buffer.InflationCountryName = CollectionOfMovie.InflationCountryName;
                Output0Buffer.ReleaseID = CollectionOfMovie.ReleaseID;
                Output0Buffer.Markets = CollectionOfMovie.Markets;
                Output0Buffer.ReleaseDate = CollectionOfMovie.ReleaseDate;
                Output0Buffer.Opening = CollectionOfMovie.Opening;
                Output0Buffer.Gross = CollectionOfMovie.Gross;
                Output0Buffer.MoviesID = CollectionOfMovie.MoviesID;
                Output0Buffer.MemberName = CollectionOfMovie.MemberName;
                Output0Buffer.Role = CollectionOfMovie.Role;
                Output0Buffer.Ranks = CollectionOfMovie.Ranks;
                Output0Buffer.Titles = CollectionOfMovie.Titles;
                Output0Buffer.Years = CollectionOfMovie.Years;
                Output0Buffer.Score = CollectionOfMovie.Score;
                Output0Buffer.MetaScore = CollectionOfMovie.MetaScore;
  
                Output0Buffer.Genre = CollectionOfMovie.Genre;

                Output0Buffer.Runtime = CollectionOfMovie.RunTime;

        }

*Expression for FileDate

SUBSTRING(@[User::JSONFileName],5,2) + "/" + SUBSTRING(@[User::JSONFileName],7,2) + "/" + SUBSTRING(@[User::JSONFileName],1,4)


*Namespaces and Code for Class C#

using System;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using System.Linq;
using System.Text;
using System.Threading.Tasks;


namespace CollectionOfMovieNameSpace
{
    class CollectionOfMovies
    {
        public string Rank { get; set; }
        public string Title { get; set; }
        public string LifeTimeGross { get; set; }
        public string Year { get; set; }
        public string MovieID { get; set; }
        public string Market { get; set; }
        public string TicketPriceName { get; set; }
        public string CurrencyCode { get; set; }
        public string InflationCountryName { get; set; }
        public string ReleaseID  {get;set;}
        public string Markets { get; set; }
        public string ReleaseDate { get; set; }
        public string Opening { get; set; }
        public string Gross { get; set; }
        public string MoviesID { get; set; }
        public string MemberName { get; set; }
        public string Role { get; set; }
        public string Ranks { get; set; }

        public string Titles { get; set; }

        public string Years { get; set; }

        public string Score { get; set; }

        public string MetaScore { get; set; }

        public string Genre { get; set; }

        public string Vote { get; set; }

        public string Director { get; set; }

        public string RunTime { get; set; }

        public string Revenue { get; set; }

        public string Description { get; set; }
        public string ReleaseType { get; set; }

        public string MovieName { get; set; }

        public string ReleaseIDs { get; set; }

        public string MoviesIDs { get; set; }

        public string MovieIDs { get; set; }

        public string MoviesName { get; set; }

        public string USDistributor { get; set; }

        public string Budget { get; set; }
        public string MPAA { get; set; }
        public string RunningTime { get; set; }
        public string Genres { get; set; }
        public string Country { get; set; }
        public string Amount { get; set; }
        public string Date { get; set; }

    }
}
